Audit fields:
- id
- actor_user_id
- actor_email
- action
- resource_type
- resource_id
- result
- ip_address
- user_agent
- metadata
- created_at

Audit these:
- login success
- login failure
- logout
- token refresh
- risk halt
- risk resume
- scheduler job create
- scheduler job run
- scheduler job delete
- IoT action requested
- content approval
- content publish request
- backtest run
- optimization run
- promotion check
- admin user action

Admin endpoints:
GET    /api/admin/audit-logs
GET    /api/admin/users
POST   /api/admin/users
PATCH  /api/admin/users/{user_id}
DELETE /api/admin/users/{user_id}
GET    /api/admin/safety-check

Metrics endpoint:
GET /api/metrics

Expose safe metrics:
- zdash_requests_total
- zdash_request_latency_ms
- zdash_errors_total
- zdash_events_total
- zdash_scheduler_jobs_total
- zdash_risk_halt_active
- zdash_backtests_total
- zdash_content_items_total
- zdash_iot_actions_total

Middleware:
- request ID middleware
- request logging middleware
- error logging middleware

Production safety checker:
If APP_ENV=production:
- DRY_RUN must remain true unless PRODUCTION_SAFETY_LOCK=false and explicit config is present.
- LIVE_TRADING_ACK cannot be enabled with default secrets.
- Social real posting requires explicit approval config.
- IoT real actions require explicit confirmation config.
- JWT_SECRET_KEY must not be default.
- DEFAULT_ADMIN_PASSWORD must not be default.
- CORS wildcard must be rejected if credentials are allowed.

Rules:
- Metrics must not expose secrets.
- Metrics endpoint requires admin if METRICS_AUTH_REQUIRED=true.
- In dev mode, local unauthenticated metrics may be allowed only if configured.
- Admin user list must never expose password hashes.
- Prefer deactivate over hard delete.
- Do not permanently delete the current authenticated admin.

Validation:
cd backend
source .venv/bin/activate
python -m ruff check app tests
python -B -m pytest -q

